Squeeze the @Steamed Brown Basmati Rice{1%pouch} to separate the grains. Tear a strip
approx 2cm along the top. Cook the rice according to pack instructions with a
#pot. Set aside until serving.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and chop the @Onion{1} into small pieces. Peel and grate
the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press).

Halve the @Bell Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Cut into 1cm chunks.
Trim the @Green Beans{80%g} and cut into thirds. Trim the @Courgette{1}, then
quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into 1cm pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan on medium heat. Once hot,
add the onion, courgette and pepper chunks and cook, stirring occasionally,
until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic, @Tikka Masala Paste{75%g} and @Tomato Puree{30%g}. Cook for
~{1%minute} more.

Pour the @Creme Fraiche{150%g}, @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%g} and @Water for the Curry{150%ml}
into the #frying pan. Bring to the boil, stirring to combine, then reduce the heat
to medium.

Stir in the green beans, then cover with a #lid (or #foil) and simmer until
the veg is almost tender, ~{8-9%minutes}.

Remove the lid, then allow the curry to simmer until thickened, stirring
occasionally, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once the curry has thickened and the veg has softened, remove from the heat.
Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of water
if it's a little too thick.

Share the rice between your #bowls. Spoon over your veggie tikka masala and
sprinkle over the @?Chilli Flakes{1%pinch} if you'd like (add less if you'd
prefer things milder). Enjoy!